Create a software bill of materials (SBOM)
body:
For government applications, it will be necessary one day to have a SBOM. We should investigate one of these to make it:
* https://pypi.org/project/ws-sbom-generator/
* https://github.com/tiiuae/sbomnix
* https://github.com/anthonyharrison/sbom4files
* https://github.com/anthonyharrison/sbom4python
* https://cyclonedx-bom-tool.readthedocs.io/en/latest/ -- may be the easiest.

Python may get one:
* https://discuss.python.org/t/software-bill-of-materials-for-next-python-release/17275

References:
* https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/types-software-bill-materials-sbom
* https://anchore.com/sbom/how-to-generate-an-sbom-with-free-open-source-tools/

title: Feature: Adding contributors section to the README.md file.
body:
There is no Contributors section in readme file .
As we know Contributions are what make the open-source community such an amazing place to learn, inspire, and create.
The Contributors section in a README.md file is important as it acknowledges and gives credit to those who have contributed to a project, fosters community and collaboration, adds transparency and accountability, and helps document the project's history for current and future maintainers. It also serves as a form of recognition, motivating contributors to continue their efforts.
![contributors](https://github.com/swirlai/swirl-search/assets/147402107/ba1e7f5f-c144-43ea-8541-6bcc9e429856)

To utilize this functionality, follow these steps:

Start Vespa Instance:
Ensure you have a running Vespa instance. If not, refer to Vespa's official documentation for installation instructions.

Add JSON File to Swirl Configuration:
Insert the provided JSON file into your Swirl configuration file.

Restart Swirl:
Restart Swirl to apply the changes.

Now, you can start searching for Vespa content. Use the following command:

swirl search vespa "my query"
